segments.name: updateActionCode
segments.description: A code representing the update action.

segments.name: entryFilerCode
segments.description: A unique code assigned by CBP to all active entry document preparers. The Entry Filer Code occupies the first three positions of an entry number regardless of where the entry is filed. This code must be the same as the Entry Filer Code in the block control header record (Record Identifier B).

segments.name: filler1
segments.description: Space fill. Reserved filler for possible future expansion of Entry Filer Code and/or Entry Number.

segments.name: entryNumber
segments.description: Unique identifying number assigned to the Entry by the Filer. For additional information on valid entry number formats, refer to Appendix E of the ACE CATAIR Chapters publication.

segments.name: entryType
segments.description: A code representing the entry type. Valid entry type codes are listed in Appendix B of the ACE CATAIR Chapters publication.

options.07: Consumption - Antidumping/ Countervailing Duty & Quota/Visa Combination 11 Informal – Free and Dutiable

segments.name: importerOfRecordType
segments.description: The type of number being used to identify the importer of record.

segments.name: importerOfRecord
segments.description: Identification of the importer of record.

segments.name: modeOfTransportationMotCode
segments.description: A code representing the mode of transportation. Valid mode of transportation codes are listed in Appendix B of the ACE CATAIR Chapters publication.

options.34: Road, other. Includes foot and animal-borne.
options.70: Fixed Transport Installations. Includes pipeline and powerhouse.

segments.name: bondTypeCode
segments.description: A code representing the bond type.

segments.name: estimatedEntryValue
segments.description: The total entered value of the entry in whole US dollars.

segments.name: plannedPortOfEntry
segments.description:
Planned / scheduled port of entry in Schedule D code.

**See Note 7 for explanation regarding input for this data element.**

Updating the value reported for Planned Port of Entry is not allowed when submitting an SE with action code “U” (Update)

Planned Port of Entry is required for entries with Non-AMs bills

segments.name: splitShipmentReleaseCode
segments.description: A code representing an option for releasing split shipments.

segments.name: portOfUnlading
segments.description:
Planned / scheduled port of unlading in Schedule D code.
Port of Unlading is required for Mail (MOT 50), Passenger Hand Carried (MOT 60), and Fixed Transport Installation (MOT 70)
